<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,253,1325]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
As the older reports actually refers to other species (
<bibRefCitation author="Redtenbacher, J." box="[751,982,253,278]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="335 - 368" refId="ref41745" refString="Redtenbacher, J. (1884) Ubersicht der Myrmeleoniden-Larven. Denkschriften, Akademie der Wissenschaften Wien, Mathematische-Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, 48, 335 - 368." type="journal article" year="1884">Redtenbacher, 1884</bibRefCitation>
), the first description of the larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was realized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Steffan, J. R." box="[465,632,289,314]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="693 - 707" refId="ref42381" refString="Steffan, J. R. (1965) Les larves de Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi), Creoleon lugduense (Villers), Neuroleon ocreatus (Navas) et N. nemausiensis (Borkh.) (Planipennes, Myrmeleontidae). Vie et Milieu, 15, 693 - 707." type="journal article" year="1965">Steffan (1965)</bibRefCitation>
. Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Cesaroni, C. &amp; Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[711,960,289,314]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="135 - 144" refId="ref39087" refString="Cesaroni, C., Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A. (2010) The larvae of Gymnocnemia variegata (Schneider, 1845) and Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi, 1790) (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae): a comparative description. In: Devetak, D., Lipovsek, S., Arnett, A. E. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 10 th International Symposium on Neuropterology (22 - 25 June 2008, Piran, Slovenia). University of Maribor, Maribor, Slovenia, pp. 135 - 144." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Cesaroni 
<emphasis box="[819,877,289,314]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed exhaustively the larva of this species comparing it with the closely related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[655,932,326,349]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Gymnocnemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[655,932,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gymnocnemia variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
